question:
Here is a real payload fragment that has caused drift:

{
  "section_id": "Part 2 Q6",
  "max_mark": 10.0,
  "question": {
    "text": "Discuss carefully, in your own words, whether you think the introduction of VAT on private schools is a good idea. Use the results from the analysis of the theoretical model to illustrate your argument and discuss the intuition behind these results. Pay particular attention to discussing which groups would benefit or lose more from the introduction of the VAT. Make references to concept studied in the lecture wherever relevant",
    "task_type": "evaluative_discussion",
    "task_goal": "Discuss carefully, in your own words, whether you think the introduction of VAT on private schools is a good idea"
  },
  "scoring": {
    "method": "classification_then_score",
    "scale": {
      "type": "likert_judgement",
      "labels": [
        "weak",
        "developing",
        "clear",
        "strong"
      ]
    },
    "criteria": [
      {
        "criterion_name": "criterion_1",
        "check": "Judge how well the response provides a corrected rewrite in the student's own tone."
      },
      {
        "criterion_name": "criterion_2",
        "check": "Judge how well the response reaches a clear and justified overall judgement."
      },
      {
        "criterion_name": "criterion_3",
        "check": "Judge how well the response uses the relevant model results, evidence, or course concepts to justify the judgement."
      },
      {
        "criterion_name": "criterion_4",
        "check": "Judge how well the response distinguishes who gains, who loses, and the main tradeoffs."
      },
      {
        "criterion_name": "criterion_5",
        "check": "Judge how well the response uses the source evidence required by the parent marking instructions."
      }
    ],
    "rules": [
      "provisional_score must be between 0 and 10.",
      "Use only this section.",
      "Choose the quality band first, then place the score within it.",
      "Reward justified correction and rewriting when asked."
    ]
  },
  "student_response": {
    "text": "6)\nIn theory, the imposition of VAT on private school fees is justified, but it is risky. Our\ntheoretical model illustrates the immediate effect. While the tax revenue can be\ncombined to increase funding for public schools, adding VAT increases the amount of\nmoney families must pay for private education, which lowers private families'\ndisposable income. The redistribution can raise overall welfare if school choices do not\nsignificantly change because public gains (spread among numerous students) may\nexceed private losses. This is consistent with the lecture discussion that public funding\ncan address inequality and capture wider social returns to education (lecture 9, 2023,\np.8).\nEvidence, however, alerts us to trade-offs. VAT raises the cost of private education and\nmay force marginal (usually middle-class) families into public schools, increasing\ncrowding, potentially lowering average quality in both sectors through composition\neffects, and raising marginal public costs. Peer effects "
  },
  "output_contract": [
    "Return keys: section_label, provisional_score, criterion_notes, strengths, weaknesses, evidence, coverage_comment.",
    "criterion_notes: list of {criterion_name, status, note}.",
    "status values: weak, developing, clear, strong.",
    "note: 2 to 5 words; do not copy criterion text.",
    "strengths and weaknesses: lists with at least 2 items each.",
    "evidence: list with at least 1 item.",
    "coverage_comment: required."
  ]
}

What in this payload is most likely to make you drift on scale meaning, score discipline, scope, and output typing? Answer under those four headings only.
